### 94

### THE PRIVY COUNCILLOR MASATSUNE

### SANGI MASATSUNE

<div style="margin-left: 32px">

  Miyoshino no  
Yama no aki kaze  
  Sayo fukete  
Furu sato samuku  
Koromo utsu nari.

AROUND Mount Miyoshino's crest  
  The autumn winds blow drear;  
The villagers are beating cloth,  
  Their merry din I hear,  
  This night so cold and clear.

</div>

<span class="small">Masatsune was a son of the writer of verse No.
[83](hvj084.htm#page_83.md); he died in the year 1221. He appears in the
illustration sitting alone in his house, listening to the sound of the
villagers beating the cloth to make it supple.</span>

